race.comment: The 2YO's kick us off and ALL ON RED (1) aims to remain unbeaten after a very impressive debut performance. He led and bolted in a fortnight ago from out wide and it's easy to think he can repeat the dose. Up in weight this time but if he can reproduce what he did fresh, it's hard to see anything turning the tables. SUPERSMASH (10) has shown good ability at the trials, winning most recently in an 850m heat at Belmont. Blinkers go on for the debut and the inside draw is usually a big tick in these 2YO races. Can be handy and put his best foot forward. ONE LAST RESORT (5) was an eye-catcher behind SUPERSMASH in that latest outing when bobbing and weaving in the closing stages. Winkers go on now and he has to be included off his trial effort. KUTE AS KAN BE (6) has trialled well since her debut performance here and was solid there. Can feature in the finish again. TEXAN DREAM (2) jumped favourite on debut and is worth another chance.
